commit.message:
pidfile(): ensure prefix path ends with slash

For some builds using Buildroot, the system default _PATH_VARRUN did not
include a trailing slas '/', which cause the pidfile() function to fail.

Example:
  pidfile("arg") => "/var/runarg.pid"

Since the __pidfile_path can be overridden we add a check if that prefix
path ends with '/', if not we add one in the path composition.

runbg: new helper function inspired by the Infix project

The runbg() function is a delayed execvp() that has double-forked to the
background (to not create zombies).  It is useful for running commands
in the background for APIs that need to return a reply, e.g. a NETCONF
RPC to reboot the system.

Compared to the original in Infix, this version double forks to reparent
itself to PID 1 (init), closes all open files, including stdio.
